==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opportune
<hw>Op`por*tune"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>opporiun</ets>, L. <ets>opportunus</ets>, lit., at or before the
port; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + a derivative of
<ets>portus</ets> port, harbor. See <er>Port</er> harbor.]</ety>
<def>Convenient; ready; hence, seasonable; timely.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is most <qex>opportune</qex> to our need.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Op`por*tune"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Op`por*tune"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opportune</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Opportune
<hw>Op`por*tune"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To suit.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr. Clerke(1637).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
